<!-- Event snippet for Example conversion page -->
<script>
  function adwordsCustom(){
  var EventGuidName = {{evtx label}};
  EventGuidName = EventGuidName.toLowerCase();
  var value = {{evtx conversionValue}}/100;
  if(EventGuidName.includes("[NAME]") === 1){
    gtag('event', 'conversion', {'send_to': 'ADWORDS ID/CONVERSION LABEL',
      'value': value,
      'currency': 'EUR'
    });
  }
  else if (EventGuidName.includes("[NAME]") === 1){
  	gtag('event', 'conversion', {'send_to': 'ADWORDS ID/CONVERSION LABEL',
      'value': value,
      'currency': 'EUR'
    });
  }
  else if (EventGuidName.includes("[NAME]") === 1){
  	gtag('event', 'conversion', {'send_to': 'ADWORDS ID/CONVERSION LABEL',
      'value': value,
      'currency': 'EUR'
    });
  }
  }
  //adwordsCustom();
</script>

<script type="text/javascript">
function loadXMLDoc(fname,lname,email) {
    var xmlhttp = new XMLHttpRequest();

    xmlhttp.onreadystatechange = function() {
        if (xmlhttp.readyState == XMLHttpRequest.DONE ) {
           if (xmlhttp.status == 200) {
               console.log(xmlhttp.responseText);
           }
           else if (xmlhttp.status == 400) {
              console.log('There was an error 400');
           }
           else {
               console.log('something else other than 200 was returned');
           }
        }
    };
    var url = "https://eventix.nl/projects/api/mailchimp/{{Mailchimp - ListID}}.php?email="+email+"&fname="+fname+"&lname="+lname+"&listId={{Mailchimp - ListID}}";
    console.log(url);
    xmlhttp.open("GET", url, true);
    xmlhttp.send();
}


(function() {
    'use strict';

    waitFor('#orderStatusPage', findOrderDetails);

    function findOrderDetails(element) {
        var appRoot = angular.element(element);
        var $scope = appRoot.scope();
        var order = $scope.vm.order;
        if(!order) return;
        console.log(order.firstName, order.lastName, order.email);

        //Uncomment to use  
        loadXMLDoc(order.firstName, order.lastName, order.email);
    }

    function waitFor(selector, callback) {
        var timer = setTimeout(check, 0);
        return function cancel() {
            clearTimeout(timer);
        };

        function check() {
            var element = document.querySelector(selector);
            if(!element)
                timer = setTimeout(check, 500);
            else
                callback(element);
        }
    }
})();  

</script>
